At level 20, I spent 45 minutes punching pyre beetles and black wolves in Nektulos Forest, trying to improve my H2H skill.<br>
<br>
Well, the skill didn't increase at all.<br>
I've read a lot about skill raising, skills cap, etc. to answer the question: &quot;Is a melee skill capped by the fighted mob's level?&quot;<br>
<br>
I found many answers, covering the whole range from &quot;yes&quot; to &quot;no&quot;.<br>
<br>
So, can anyone help me answering that question?<br>
Can I improve my H2H level by punching level 1 mobs?<br>
Is there any kind of cap such as (mobLevel + 1)*5?<br>
<br>
(Yeah I know i just have to find a group that grant me to punch the mobs they pull, but WTF with the pyre beetles?)<br>
<br>
I'll trade a stack of /kneel for any answer, thank you.<br>
<br>
P.S: don't hesitate to /flame if this isn't the right place to ask... :-) <p><BR>
Laroos, Dark Elf Wizard on Vallon Zek<BR>
Aegish, Dark Elf Wizard on Firiona Vie. <BR><BR>
"Have you ever tried dwarf sandwiches?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udaliondveldrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalion DVeldrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/02 6:54:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raising melee skills: definitive answer? (OOC)</span><hr size=1> From what i've been told, practicing skills on green mobs do not help you to get better at them (except disarm i believe). You should practice your skills on light-blue or higher mobs, though at light blue, there will be very few skill increases. Hope this helps *shrug*. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=209679><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/teneel/Dalion.jpg></a><br><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/teneel/Nagafen2.jpg><br> Harbinger of Vengeance<br><i> ~* He who follows his heart will find that it will bleed *~</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/02 12:27:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raising melee skills: definitive answer? (OOC)</span><hr size=1> If you can't get experience from the kill (green), you cannot raise your skills.<br>
<br>
I think back in the past, Soulbinders used to be of a level where anyone could autoattack, go afk, and get weapon increases.  The Souldbinders do not attack back, so it was easy RvR.  Of course, now they are a level 1 mob, so it was considered an exploit.<br>
<br>
There is still at least one level 60+ mobs that let you get skill increases on it... but it's not entirely practical, and he's magic anyways, so no h2h for anyone other than monks.<br>
<br>
Anyways, the easiest way is to just practice when you can't get into a group.  I used to practice throwing on mobs in Velks when I couldn't find a group.  At least it was some entertainment.<br>
<br>
-=Viren=- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 968<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/02 2:46:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raising melee skills: definitive answer? (OOC)</span><hr size=1> I can 100% confirm that I did gain some offense skill fighting green-con mobs with my new paladin.  I double checked the /con after I saw the skill gain just to make sure.  It was green (not teal).  <br>
<br>
Not sure if it's different in the lower levels, or if it was because it was a high green, but I definately did gain skill.  I don't recall ever gaining skill from green cons with my higher level characters.<br>
<br>
Typically though, the vast majority of my skill gain comes from blue and up mobs.  I gained 1 point of defense and offense each during some of the many times I attacked the Priest of Dischord to refresh my mana, so it would seem there's no upper limit on who you can gain skill from (PoD's gotta be at least 40-50 levels above me).<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/02 3:38:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raising melee skills: definitive answer? (OOC)</span><hr size=1> At low levels you get xp from some green mobs.  Like in the level 6-9 range I think before you have multiple layers of blue, etc, somehow you can get xp from an occasional green.<br>
<br>
-=Viren=- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uptitlarousse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PtitLarousse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 2:20:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raising melee skills: definitive answer? (OOC)</span><hr size=1> Thank you everyone for the given clues...<br>
<br>
I punched red giants at Giant Fort (WW) for 30 minutes, then I went to light blue rock dervishes in Lavastorm, I finally tried the 10ish flying red things at Lavastorm (don't remember the name).<br>
<br>
No improvement at all, 2 hours spent. H2H is still at level 1 (I put 1 point in it, kind of &quot;melee skill boot disk&quot;)<br>
<br>
My advice is:<br>
Boot disks never work (melee or W98), you have to reinstall if you want to add features =)  (my 2cp joke).<br>
If you want to increase all your melee skills, do it as soon as you can, as soon as you DING.<br>
<br>
If you do it later, it's gonna be a pain in the -beeeeep-.<br>
<br>
Thank you everyone, I hope that this mini thread helped lots of player, not only me.<br>
 <p><BR>
Laroos, Dark Elf Wizard on Vallon Zek<BR>
Aegish, Dark Elf Wizard on Firiona Vie. <BR><BR>
"Have you ever tried dwarf sandwiches?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1169<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/21/02 4:57:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raising melee skills: definitive answer? (OOC)</span><hr size=1> If you still want to get that skill up, try to find a nice high level shaman and follow them as they solo.  Get Harnessing of Spirit or some other dex buff, and a haste buff, and whack away.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A> at: 8/21/02 4:58:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uptitlarousse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PtitLarousse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/27/02 2:03:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> And what with PvP?</span><hr size=1> Hmm... just another thing, to make this thread live longer...<br>
