"Have you ever tried dwarf sandwiches?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalnin>Dalnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/27/02 10:13:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: And what with PvP?</span><hr size=1> to get skill ups pvp you need to be fighting an npc, usually mage pets .... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uptitlarousse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PtitLarousse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/10/02 1:48:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> [PvP, melee, skills] All pet classes?</span><hr size=1> Hello guys (and girls), i bring this thread back to life, just to get a little more info.<br>
<br>
You have to fight an npc to raise your skills, that's ok. &quot;Mage pet&quot;, ok. So I guess (and hope) it will work with beastlord, necro, shadowknight and enchanter pet. Am I right?? <p><BR>
Laroos, Dark Elf Wizard on Vallon Zek<BR>
Aegish, Dark Elf Wizard on Firiona Vie. <BR><BR>
"Have you ever tried dwarf sandwiches?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukhiraz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khiraz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/10/02 6:09:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: [PvP, melee, skills] All pet classes?</span><hr size=1> I would assume so. At least I can vouch for the beastlord's pet; I've set her to sparring with a few people now, and they recieved raises in both offensive and defensive skills.<br>
<br>
Oh, one bit of advice for the pet owner: Don't *ahem* leave the computer to make a sandwich while someone's fighting your pet. When you're not looking, they get tougher (Sorry Cyth, wherever you are ;-) ).<br>
