Patriarch of Cabilis<br>
Skathris Ven'Sho<br>
Oh, To Be as L33t as My Wolf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwardenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wardenn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ring20.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wildwunner!</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/16/02 5:19:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: [PvP, melee, skills] All pet classes?</span><hr size=1> At the moment, Im in my 35th season as a rogue. My back stab skill level should be about 160 or so. At the moment, I have gotten it up to 151 from 130. The majority of what helped doing that was Dex. My dex, before I got some good dex stuff, was only 117, sad for a rogue. Anyway, now its 150-160, depending on my weapon choices, and my backstab goes up often and my 1HS went from 26-100 in a about 3 days. <br>
<br>
Anyway, the point of my rambling is that DEX helps alot in raising your melee skills. Though you DO have to fight light-dark blue mobs <p>Warden Wildrunner
